The Inspector-General of Police, Usman Baba, paid a condolence visit to the widow and family of the late DIG Joseph Egbunike at their Abuja residence. The IGP was on Wednesday accompanied by other members of the Force Management Team. Baba urged the family to be strong and focused on upholding the legacies of the deceased. He restated that the late DIG was a man of knowledge, resourcefulness, commitment and diligence in his lifetime.  Baba said the Force is “generally pained” to have lost a dedicated senior officer who put in 34 years and 7 months of meritorious service to Nigeria. The police chief disclosed that deliberations are in top gear to, in conjunction with the family, arrange befitting burial rites for Egbunike.